                            ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
                             PLZ-MEDIA-TYPE
                            ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━


[https://img.shields.io/badge/license-GPL_3-green.svg]
[http://elpa.gnu.org/packages/plz-media-type.svg]
[https://github.com/r0man/plz-media-type/actions/workflows/test.yml/badge.svg]

`plz-media-type' is an Emacs Lisp library that enhances MIME type
handling for HTTP requests within Emacs. It leverages the [plz.el] HTTP
library for networking calls and introduces a mechanism to process
responses based on the content type header. This library defines various
classes and methods for parsing and processing standard MIME types,
including JSON, XML, HTML, and binary data. It is used in the [LLM]
library to handle decoding of various streaming and non-streaming media
type formats.

• Package name (GNU ELPA): plz-media-type
• Official manual:
  [https://github.com/r0man/plz-media-type/blob/main/plz-media-type.org]
• Git repository: [https://github.com/r0man/plz-media-type]


